OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784593081
OL,3,CWorld Cup final 2026: Match underway
OL,4,Cas Spain and Argentina fight to lift
OL,5,Ctrophy
OL,7,FArgentina has a streak worth noting as
OL,8,Fwell. It has won seven consecutive
OL,9,FWorld Cup matches, tied with Italy for
OL,10,Fthe second-longest such run in men's
OL,11,Ftournament history. Only Brazil, which
OL,12,Fwon 11 straight spanning 2002 and
OL,13,F2006, has a longer World Cup winning
OL,14,Fstreak.
OL,16,FThe game is just the second head-to-
OL,17,Fhead meeting in a World Cup between
OL,18,FArgentina and Spain. Argentina won 2-1
OL,19,Fin the 1966 group stage.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
